subclause.title: SubClause
subclause.p: Water-to-air unitary air-conditioners with a rated capacity greater than or equal to 65 kW, including packaged air-conditioners, split system, and variable refrigerant flow units, must have a minimum energy efficiency ratio of 4.0 Wr/Winput power for cooling when tested in accordance with AS/NZS ISO 13256.1 at test condition C3, where input power includes both compressor and fan input power.Unitary air-conditioning equipment including packaged air-conditioners, split systems, and variable refrigerant flow systems must comply with MEPS and for a capacity greater than or equal to 65 kWr—

ol.xt:author: Lee Liu
ol.li: where water cooled, have a minimum energy efficiency ratio of 4.0 Wr/Winput power for cooling when tested in accordance with AS/NZS 3823.1.2 at test condition T1, where input power includes both compressor and fan input power; or

where air cooled, have a minimum energy efficiency ratio of 2.9 Wr/Winput power for cooling when tested in accordance with AS/NZS 3823.1.2 at test condition T1, where input power includes both compressor and fan input power.

subclause.title: SubClause
subclause.p: Where the weighted efficiency index contribution of an air conditioner is assessed using the formula at (2)(a), air-cooled unitary air-conditioners, including packaged air-conditioners, split systems, and variable refrigerant flow units, must have—

ol.xt:author: Jerome Samuel
ol.li:
at least one—
digital scroll compressor; or
inverter driven compressor.

subclause.xt:author: Jerome Samuel
subclause.title: SubClause
subclause.p: The compressor in 3(b) must be sized sufficiently to allow the unit to modulate across 50% to 100% of its rated cooling capacity.

subclause.title: SubClause
subclause.num: 45The requirements of (2) to (4) do not apply to the following:

ol.xt:author: Lee Liu
ol.li: Unitary air-conditioners with a rated cooling capacity of less than 10 kW.
Unitary air-conditioners that serve only one sole-occupancy unit in a Class 2 building.

callout.xt:author: Jerome Samuel
callout.p: Variable refrigerant flow and multi-split units are tested as representative combination.
